entry.title: COVID-19 Growth Analysis
entry.content:
#collapse-hide

def plot_countries(df, countries, min_cases=100, ls='-', col='cases'):
    for country in countries:
        (df.loc[(df.country == country) & (df.cases >= min_cases)]
         .reset_index()[col]
         .plot(label=country, ls=ls)
        )

sns.set_palette(sns.hls_palette(8, l=.45, s=.8)) # 8 countries max
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))

countries = ['Italy', 'US (total)', 'Germany', 'France', 'Spain', 'United Kingdom (total)', 
             'Poland', 'Iran']
plot_countries(df_confirmed, countries)

asian_countries = ['Singapore', 'Japan', 'Korea, South', 'Hong Kong'] 
plot_countries(df_confirmed, asian_countries, ls='--')

x = np.linspace(0, plt.xlim()[1] - 1)
plt.plot(x, 100 * (1.33) ** x, ls='--', color='k', label='33% daily growth')

plt.yscale('log');
plt.title('Data up to {}'.format(df_confirmed.index.max().strftime('%B %d, %Y')))
plt.xlabel('Days from first 100 confirmed cases')
plt.ylabel('Confirmed cases (log scale)')
ax.get_yaxis().set_major_formatter(matplotlib.ticker.ScalarFormatter())
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.0, 1.0))
sns.despine()
plt.annotate('Based on COVID Data Repository by Johns Hopkins CSSE\nBy Thomas Wiecki', 
             (0.05, 0.0), xycoords='figure fraction', fontsize=10);


#collapse-hide
sns.set_palette(sns.hls_palette(8, l=.45, s=.8)) # 8 countries max
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))

# 28000 intensiv, 80% belegt
icu_germany = 28000 #* .2

df_tmp = df_confirmed.loc[lambda x: (x.country == 'Germany') & (x.cases > 100)].cases_crit
df_tmp.plot(ax=ax)

x = np.linspace(0, 30, 30)
pd.Series(index=pd.date_range(df_tmp.index[0], periods=30),
          data=100*p_crit * (1.33) ** x).plot(ls='--', color='k', label='33% daily growth')

plt.axhline(icu_germany, color='.3', ls='-.', label='Total ICU beds')
plt.axhline(icu_germany * .2, color='.5', ls=':', label='Free ICU beds')
plt.yscale('log');
plt.title('When will Germany run out of ICU beds?')
#plt.xlabel('Days from first 100 confirmed cases')
plt.ylabel('Expected critical cases (log scale)')
ax.get_yaxis().set_major_formatter(matplotlib.ticker.ScalarFormatter())
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.0, 1.0))
sns.despine()
plt.annotate('Based on COVID Data Repository by Johns Hopkins CSSE by {}\nBy Thomas Wiecki'.format(df_confirmed.index.max().strftime('%B %d, %Y')), 
             (0.05, 0.0), xycoords='figure fraction', fontsize=10);


#collapse-hide

df_confirmed['pct_change'] = df_confirmed.groupby('country').cases.pct_change().rolling(5).mean()

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 8))
df_confirmed.set_index('country', append=True).loc[(slice(None), countries), :].loc[lambda x: x.cases > 100].reset_index().set_index('days_since_100').groupby('country')['pct_change'].plot()
df_confirmed.set_index('country', append=True).loc[(slice(None), asian_countries), :].loc[lambda x: x.cases > 100].reset_index().set_index('days_since_100').groupby('country')['pct_change'].plot(ls='--')
plt.ylim(0, 1)
plt.xlim(0, 20)
plt.axhline(.33, ls='--', color='k')
plt.legend()

plt.title('Data up to {}'.format(df_confirmed.index.max().strftime('%B %d, %Y')))
plt.xlabel('Days from first 100 confirmed cases')
plt.ylabel('Percent change from previous # of confirmed')
ax.get_yaxis().set_major_formatter(matplotlib.ticker.ScalarFormatter())
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.0, 1.0))
sns.despine()
plt.annotate('Based on COVID Data Repository by Johns Hopkins CSSE\nBy Thomas Wiecki', 
             (0.05, 0.0), xycoords='figure fraction', fontsize=10);

entry.title: COVID-19 Growth By State (US)
entry.content:
#collapse-hide
for case_threshold in [30, 100]:
    df = US_cities[US_cities['Total'] > case_threshold].sort_values(by='Total')
    df = df.drop(['Province/State', 'Country/Region', 'Lat', 'Long', 'Total'], axis=1)
    cols = list(df)
    df = df[cols[-2:] + cols[:-2]]
    states = df.melt(id_vars=['Area','State'], var_name='date', value_name='cases_confirmed')
    pivoted = states.groupby(['State', 'date'], as_index=False).sum().pivot('date', 'State').cumsum()
    cleaned = pivoted.reset_index().cases_confirmed
    cols = []

    for col in cleaned:
        cols.append(cleaned[col][cleaned[col] > case_threshold].dropna().reset_index()[col])

    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16, 8))
    ax = plt.axes()
    pd.concat(cols, axis=1, names=list(cleaned)).plot(ax=ax, marker='o', logy=True)
    plt.title('COVID19 Growth in US states')
    plt.ylabel('Cumulative confirmed cases (log scale)')
    plt.xlabel(f'Number of days since {case_threshold}th case')
    plt.annotate('Based on COVID Data Repository by Johns Hopkins CSSE\nBy Avy Faingezicht, @avyfain', 
                 (0.07, 0.02), xycoords='figure fraction', fontsize=10);
    plt.legend(loc="lower right")
    if case_threshold == 100:
        x = np.linspace(0, plt.xlim()[1] - 1)
        plt.plot(x, 100 * (1.33) ** x, ls='--', color='k', label='33% daily growth')
        plt.annotate('33% Daily Growth', 
                     (0.85, 0.9), xycoords='figure fraction', fontsize=10);

Updated hourly by GitHub Actions.

This visualization was made by Avy Faingezicht1.

  1. Data sourced from "2019 Novel Coronavirus COVID-19 (2019-nCoV) Data Repository by Johns Hopkins CSSE" GitHub repository. Link to original notebook.↩
